1
00:00:10,328 --> 00:00:12,960
Why do I keep seeing you at Nao's house so often?
Don't tell me...

2
00:00:13,106 --> 00:00:16,324
- you're hitting on Nue too.
- At first, I didn't think so either.

3
00:00:16,728 --> 00:00:19,773
- But now I'm starting to think it.
- You're seriously out of your mind, asshole.

4
00:00:19,817 --> 00:00:21,746
And those guys think you're some mafia boss too.

5
00:00:21,835 --> 00:00:23,022
Come work with me.

6
00:00:23,448 --> 00:00:24,231
Dad ordered it.

7
00:00:24,730 --> 00:00:27,346
- I'm not going.
- Go change your clothes.

8
00:00:33,328 --> 00:00:34,915
I already did it.

9
00:00:36,582 --> 00:00:38,684
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

10
00:01:07,293 --> 00:01:08,395
Feeling better yet?

11
00:01:10,213 --> 00:01:11,133
Nao.

12
00:01:13,835 --> 00:01:15,951
Why aren't you asking me anything?

13
00:01:18,306 --> 00:01:20,146
You only asked if I was okay.

14
00:01:20,822 --> 00:01:22,293
If I got hurt anywhere.

15
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:25,795
You came back looking like this.

16
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:27,724
What else am I supposed to ask?

17
00:01:30,857 --> 00:01:31,826
Thanks.

18
00:01:43,137 --> 00:01:45,066
So you're really not hurting anywhere anymore, right?

19
00:01:49,573 --> 00:01:50,631
And besides...

20
00:01:51,035 --> 00:01:52,671
I just trust you.

21
00:01:53,928 --> 00:01:54,840
I don't know.

22
00:01:55,511 --> 00:01:58,515
I just feel like I can trust you.

23
00:01:59,884 --> 00:02:01,066
That's why I don't want to ask.

24
00:02:02,973 --> 00:02:03,946
I...

25
00:02:04,720 --> 00:02:06,155
Thank you so much.

26
00:02:34,928 --> 00:02:36,200
I'll take care of him myself.

27
00:02:36,546 --> 00:02:37,186
Alright.

28
00:02:58,760 --> 00:02:59,755
Singha.

29
00:03:00,897 --> 00:03:01,831
Hey, Singha.

30
00:03:03,897 --> 00:03:04,800
What?

31
00:03:05,768 --> 00:03:08,777
- Why are you yelling when I'm this close?
- And what the hell are you spacing out about?

32
00:03:09,288 --> 00:03:11,035
I've been calling you forever. Didn't you hear me?

33
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:14,466
What's wrong? Stressed about work?

34
00:03:16,826 --> 00:03:17,835
Then what is it?

35
00:03:18,804 --> 00:03:20,182
Fought with your little brother?

36
00:03:20,431 --> 00:03:22,084
Wait, no.

37
00:03:23,346 --> 00:03:25,262
You never fight with your brother.

38
00:03:25,622 --> 00:03:27,137
Because you've never been nice to him.

39
00:03:30,964 --> 00:03:32,120
So what happened?

40
00:03:33,311 --> 00:03:34,755
Suer already did it.

41
00:03:37,213 --> 00:03:38,448
I forced him to.

42
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:41,542
Isn't that too soon?

43
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,475
Dad ordered it this time.

44
00:03:45,893 --> 00:03:47,791
He even sent people to keep an eye on me.

45
00:03:48,231 --> 00:03:50,000
If I couldn't force him into it,

46
00:03:50,902 --> 00:03:52,977
Dad would've come and forced him himself.

47
00:03:56,964 --> 00:03:58,613
What should I do, Ben?

48
00:03:59,982 --> 00:04:03,506
I still can't get the image of him shaking out of my head.

49
00:04:06,915 --> 00:04:09,568
I think your brother probably hates you even more now.

50
00:04:11,662 --> 00:04:12,480
Hey.

51
00:04:13,653 --> 00:04:16,324
- Wanna look for a new job?
- Yeah, I do.

52
00:04:16,902 --> 00:04:19,995
I wanna quit. I'm sick of my stubborn boss.

53
00:04:20,528 --> 00:04:21,791
Go to hell, Ben.

54
00:04:26,551 --> 00:04:28,595
I get that Dad forced you.

55
00:04:29,248 --> 00:04:30,511
But what I don't get is...

56
00:04:30,915 --> 00:04:33,911
why can't you just explain things properly to your brother?

57
00:04:35,004 --> 00:04:36,644
Your relationship with him

58
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:38,182
wouldn't be this bad.

59
00:04:41,453 --> 00:04:47,688
Oh right, I forgot.
The future big boss can't explain himself.

60
00:04:47,940 --> 00:04:50,755
- He can't afford to go soft.
- He'll get cocky.

61
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,586
You dumbass. No wonder...

62
00:04:52,684 --> 00:04:56,053
- your brother doesn't love you.
- You can say whatever you want about me,

63
00:04:56,417 --> 00:04:59,310
- but don't say my brother doesn't love me.
- Why not, Mr. Unloved Brother?

64
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:02,920
- Didn't you hear? Tiger hates you.
- You hate me that much?

65
00:05:03,168 --> 00:05:04,791
There's no way it'd be as much

66
00:05:05,048 --> 00:05:08,177
- as Tiger hates you.
- Stop rubbing it in already.

67
00:05:08,693 --> 00:05:10,657
I'm already dying inside.

68
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:12,862
Here we go again.

69
00:05:13,128 --> 00:05:16,773
I really want other people to see you like this.
The terrifying mafia boss

70
00:05:17,128 --> 00:05:20,262
secretly sitting here crying because his brother doesn't love him.

71
00:05:22,146 --> 00:05:27,284
But you do feel awful about forcing your brother today, don't you?

72
00:05:30,973 --> 00:05:32,835
I think you already did your best.

73
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:37,120
The boss gave the order, didn't he?

74
00:05:39,906 --> 00:05:42,857
Even if he doesn't know you're protecting him,

75
00:05:43,377 --> 00:05:46,746
at least your brother's safe.

76
00:05:49,231 --> 00:05:51,306
I wonder how he's doing right now.

77
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:54,168
- Then call him.
- No way.

78
00:05:55,008 --> 00:05:57,893
- He'll know I love him.
- What the hell is wrong with you?

79
00:05:58,337 --> 00:06:00,702
I'm seriously so sick of you...

80
00:06:01,031 --> 00:06:04,740
You're so damn stubborn.
In front of him, you act all tough.

81
00:06:04,840 --> 00:06:07,466
Always teasing and provoking him every single day.

82
00:06:07,777 --> 00:06:11,324
But when he gets mad, you sit here crying like this.

83
00:06:11,542 --> 00:06:12,982
Then what do you want me to do?

84
00:06:14,097 --> 00:06:16,755
You want me to keep comforting him?

85
00:06:17,391 --> 00:06:18,924
How's he supposed to survive then?

86
00:06:20,111 --> 00:06:21,866
I can't protect him forever.

87
00:06:25,386 --> 00:06:27,982
You should worry more about that kid I told you to investigate.

88
00:08:11,471 --> 00:08:12,724
Whoa.

89
00:08:12,857 --> 00:08:14,986
Hey, Suer. Wake up.

90
00:08:18,315 --> 00:08:19,586
Hey, wake up.

91
00:08:19,928 --> 00:08:22,800
- Why are you being so loud?
- It's already six in the morning.

92
00:08:22,986 --> 00:08:26,320
- Huh? Why didn't you wake me up?
- You stayed up late last night.

93
00:08:26,688 --> 00:08:30,293
- I didn't help prepare the shop at all.
- Yeah, yeah. Go shower or you'll be late.

94
00:08:32,408 --> 00:08:33,275
Ow.

95
00:08:44,564 --> 00:08:46,040
Aren't you boys gonna eat first?

96
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,660
We gotta hurry.

97
00:08:48,177 --> 00:08:48,995
Good morning.

98
00:08:49,213 --> 00:08:53,066
- Tiger, what happened? Your eyes are so swollen.
- Oh...

99
00:08:53,155 --> 00:08:56,213
I've been eating too much salty food lately.

100
00:08:56,977 --> 00:09:00,471
Cut down on sodium, okay? Or the renal disease is gonna come for you.

101
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:01,937
Yes.

102
00:09:03,524 --> 00:09:05,300
Sodium my ass.

103
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:10,226
Last night, your tears and snot got all over my sleeve.

104
00:09:10,795 --> 00:09:12,408
Stop teasing me.

105
00:09:12,911 --> 00:09:15,493
Let's go to class.
We'll head out first.

106
00:09:15,577 --> 00:09:19,644
- Study hard, boys.
- Yes. Bye, Mom.

107
00:09:31,373 --> 00:09:32,693
- Suer.
- Hmm?

108
00:09:33,266 --> 00:09:34,737
I like having you around.

109
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:36,231
Mom and Dan do too.

110
00:09:38,737 --> 00:09:41,164
No, I just got worried that

111
00:09:41,408 --> 00:09:42,937
you'd think we don't want you here.

112
00:09:43,328 --> 00:09:45,568
Having you here is great.

113
00:09:45,822 --> 00:09:47,128
There's someone to help with work,

114
00:09:47,453 --> 00:09:49,635
play games and watch movies with.

115
00:09:50,097 --> 00:09:52,340
The atmosphere's way more lively.

116
00:09:52,862 --> 00:09:55,080
So no matter what happens,

117
00:09:55,488 --> 00:09:57,235
you can always come back here.

118
00:09:58,986 --> 00:10:00,180
That's all I wanted to say.

119
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:26,262
Hello.

120
00:10:26,422 --> 00:10:27,764
Are you Duennao?

121
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:31,315
Yeah. Who are you?

122
00:10:32,408 --> 00:10:36,360
I'm Manao. I wanna be friends with you.

123
00:10:37,146 --> 00:10:38,346
Is something wrong?

124
00:10:38,791 --> 00:10:39,302
Hey.

125
00:10:40,044 --> 00:10:42,090
Who's that? Do you know her, Duen?

126
00:10:43,777 --> 00:10:44,515
Well...

127
00:10:44,777 --> 00:10:47,524
maybe she likes you and just wanted to talk.

128
00:10:48,631 --> 00:10:50,840
- She likes me?
- Yeah.

129
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:52,968
But if you're not interested, you don't have to reply.

130
00:10:53,204 --> 00:10:54,706
Just focus on studying for now.

131
00:10:55,964 --> 00:10:56,977
The teacher's looking over here.

132
00:11:05,613 --> 00:11:07,577
How was class today? Tired?

133
00:11:10,444 --> 00:11:11,831
- Nao.
- Hmm?

134
00:11:12,111 --> 00:11:13,248
Come on, let's practice.

135
00:11:14,031 --> 00:11:15,017
Yeah.

136
00:11:21,346 --> 00:11:23,448
Whoa, nice.

137
00:11:25,675 --> 00:11:26,951
Go, go!

138
00:11:27,044 --> 00:11:29,160
Nice!

139
00:11:29,613 --> 00:11:30,417
Nice.

140
00:11:35,706 --> 00:11:37,737
- We're home.
- Welcome back.

141
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:41,040
- You're back already? Hungry?
- We're back, Mom.

142
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,462
- Here, let me help.
- Just a little.

143
00:11:42,542 --> 00:11:44,453
- Thanks.
- I'll go find something for you to eat.

144
00:11:44,635 --> 00:11:47,200
Mom, Coach complimented me today.

145
00:11:47,257 --> 00:11:49,404
Really? What did Coach say?

146
00:11:49,542 --> 00:11:51,431
Coach said I'm really good.

147
00:11:51,706 --> 00:11:55,235
- Once the competition comes, I'll definitely be a top contender.
- Wow.

148
00:11:55,435 --> 00:11:57,404
Whose kid is this? Why are you so talented?

149
00:11:58,017 --> 00:12:01,155
I'm your kid, Mom.

150
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,871
And Dan's bro too.

151
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:04,848
Aww.

152
00:12:05,862 --> 00:12:06,573
Come on.

153
00:12:06,755 --> 00:12:08,031
What do you wanna eat tonight?

154
00:12:13,062 --> 00:12:14,884
So no matter what happens,

155
00:12:14,991 --> 00:12:16,897
you can always come back here.

156
00:12:30,924 --> 00:12:31,760
Hey.

157
00:12:33,613 --> 00:12:34,844
Can't sleep again?

158
00:12:40,008 --> 00:12:40,955
What about you?

159
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:42,595
Why aren't you asleep yet?

160
00:12:43,942 --> 00:12:46,528
- Don't tell me you're hungry again.
- No.

161
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:48,693
I just came down to get some water.

162
00:12:51,155 --> 00:12:52,004
Nao.

163
00:12:53,155 --> 00:12:53,742
Hmm?

164
00:12:55,835 --> 00:12:57,302
I...

165
00:12:59,431 --> 00:13:01,088
Can I talk to you about something?

166
00:13:09,684 --> 00:13:10,782
Aren't you scared?

167
00:13:13,235 --> 00:13:13,937
Scared of what?

168
00:13:15,075 --> 00:13:15,853
Me.

169
00:13:18,613 --> 00:13:20,551
Coming back covered in blood.

170
00:13:21,235 --> 00:13:23,106
I might've done something bad.

171
00:13:23,506 --> 00:13:25,791
I could hurt you and your family too.

172
00:13:27,382 --> 00:13:29,266
- But would you?
- Never.

173
00:13:29,924 --> 00:13:30,951
Then that's all that matters.

174
00:13:35,431 --> 00:13:36,995
I've told you before.

175
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,924
I trust you.

176
00:13:40,671 --> 00:13:42,293
If I told you everything,

177
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,093
would you still stay with me?

178
00:13:44,982 --> 00:13:47,995
- I mean...
- If you're not ready, you can tell me later.

179
00:13:48,124 --> 00:13:50,853
- Don't force yourself.
- I don't wanna keep it to myself anymore.

180
00:13:51,168 --> 00:13:52,337
And besides...

181
00:13:53,035 --> 00:13:54,715
I've already started believing

182
00:13:55,875 --> 00:13:57,297
that you won't leave me.

183
00:14:02,173 --> 00:14:04,222
I went to work for my family.

184
00:14:06,706 --> 00:14:07,671
Kill him.

185
00:14:10,813 --> 00:14:12,431
You refused to do it last time.

186
00:14:13,662 --> 00:14:15,060
You can't avoid it this time.

187
00:14:16,466 --> 00:14:17,804
Why does it have to be me?

188
00:14:18,857 --> 00:14:20,773
Because sooner or later, you'll have to do it anyway.

189
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:24,768
Please spare me.

190
00:14:26,235 --> 00:14:30,026
Please don't hurt me. I'm begging you.

191
00:14:30,657 --> 00:14:32,151
Please spare my life.

192
00:14:40,540 --> 00:14:41,302
Singha.

193
00:14:42,413 --> 00:14:43,488
I'm begging you.

194
00:14:44,460 --> 00:14:45,386
I don't wanna do it.

195
00:14:45,746 --> 00:14:47,791
If you don't do it, you'll be next.

196
00:14:49,426 --> 00:14:50,568
You wouldn't kill me.

197
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,751
Are you sure about that?

198
00:14:55,177 --> 00:14:56,288
If you can't do it,

199
00:14:56,951 --> 00:14:58,013
then you're useless.

200
00:15:00,488 --> 00:15:01,515
Take it.

201
00:15:04,813 --> 00:15:05,720
Hurry up.

202
00:15:13,088 --> 00:15:13,786
Shoot.

203
00:15:14,208 --> 00:15:17,328
Please don't hurt me. I'm begging you.

204
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,511
Please...

205
00:15:34,875 --> 00:15:37,420
I told you to shoot.

206
00:15:40,635 --> 00:15:42,946
Back then, my mind just went completely blank.

207
00:15:43,795 --> 00:15:45,315
Before I knew it,

208
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,573
I ended up back here.

209
00:15:50,688 --> 00:15:52,497
Maybe it's because I really like this place.

210
00:15:53,808 --> 00:15:55,546
I want a warm home.

211
00:15:56,217 --> 00:15:57,991
A place where people care about each other.

212
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,191
Even the little things.

213
00:16:04,373 --> 00:16:06,355
Honestly, I...

214
00:16:11,155 --> 00:16:13,315
never wanted to be the son of a mafia boss.

215
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,288
Mm.

216
00:16:18,057 --> 00:16:19,533
You're still you, Suer.

217
00:16:19,826 --> 00:16:23,631
I don't know what you've done behind everyone's backs,

218
00:16:23,942 --> 00:16:25,680
but the Suer I know...

219
00:16:26,084 --> 00:16:28,617
you're the guy who spends all day teasing me.

220
00:16:29,635 --> 00:16:31,226
Even though you can be

221
00:16:32,768 --> 00:16:34,386
kind of an asshole sometimes,

222
00:16:35,257 --> 00:16:36,644
you're still Suer.

223
00:16:36,893 --> 00:16:39,480
The guy who's always looking out for the people around him.

224
00:16:40,004 --> 00:16:42,422
That's the Suer I know.

225
00:16:45,973 --> 00:16:47,871
And I still mean what I said.

226
00:16:48,142 --> 00:16:51,217
You can always come back here.

227
00:16:57,000 --> 00:16:58,226
But now I know.

228
00:17:00,404 --> 00:17:02,382
I can't keep running away forever.

229
00:17:03,377 --> 00:17:05,364
I'm scared the people around me

230
00:17:05,840 --> 00:17:06,853
will leave me.

231
00:17:09,213 --> 00:17:10,955
Because something dangerous might happen.

232
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:13,460
Then protect me.

233
00:17:15,915 --> 00:17:16,533
Can you?

234
00:17:18,844 --> 00:17:20,488
If we really matter to you,

235
00:17:21,062 --> 00:17:22,173
Nao,

236
00:17:23,653 --> 00:17:25,220
Mick and Field too,

237
00:17:26,497 --> 00:17:28,257
then don't be scared for us.

238
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,586
Just protect us.

239
00:17:32,608 --> 00:17:34,426
Or if you don't want to protect us anymore,

240
00:17:35,857 --> 00:17:37,422
then leave us behind.

241
00:17:38,511 --> 00:17:39,457
But you...

242
00:17:39,817 --> 00:17:41,693
don't abandon yourself, okay?

243
00:17:43,311 --> 00:17:44,502
At the very least,

244
00:17:45,382 --> 00:17:47,537
protect yourself from danger.

245
00:17:49,097 --> 00:17:50,022
Okay?

246
00:17:51,248 --> 00:17:53,288
That's all I'm asking from you.

247
00:18:01,342 --> 00:18:03,231
I don't wanna live like this anymore, Nao.

248
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,502
I'll protect

249
00:18:06,013 --> 00:18:07,022
myself

250
00:18:08,942 --> 00:18:10,555
and the people important to me too.

251
00:18:13,848 --> 00:18:14,884
Thank you.

252
00:18:17,675 --> 00:18:18,577
Mm.

253
00:18:20,644 --> 00:18:21,533
So?

254
00:18:22,337 --> 00:18:23,626
Feeling better now?

255
00:18:28,555 --> 00:18:31,440
Then I'm going upstairs to sleep.

256
00:18:33,297 --> 00:18:34,253
Wait.

257
00:18:36,928 --> 00:18:39,386
I was thinking of finding something to watch.

258
00:18:40,968 --> 00:18:42,053
Wanna watch together?

259
00:18:42,293 --> 00:18:44,946
Mm, okay.

260
00:19:48,871 --> 00:19:50,857
Nao. Hey, Nao.

261
00:19:51,244 --> 00:19:53,106
Shit, you scared the hell out of me.

262
00:19:54,257 --> 00:19:56,591
If you're sleepy, just go upstairs and sleep.

263
00:20:00,102 --> 00:20:00,937
Yeah.

264
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:03,795
- Good night.
- Mm.

265
00:20:16,857 --> 00:20:17,613
Shit.

266
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:13,511
Friendly Football Tournament

267
00:21:25,106 --> 00:21:26,653
A little to the left.

268
00:21:29,035 --> 00:21:32,302
That guy's acting cocky as hell. I'm definitely going after him.

269
00:21:40,020 --> 00:21:41,662
You all remember our game plan, right?

270
00:21:41,980 --> 00:21:43,644
Play exactly like we practiced.

271
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,035
And most importantly,

272
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:47,520
don't start any fights with the other team.

273
00:21:47,737 --> 00:21:49,235
No matter how much they provoke you,

274
00:21:49,395 --> 00:21:51,555
stay calm. Avoid it if you can.

275
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:52,697
Got it?

276
00:21:55,364 --> 00:21:56,293
Tiger.

277
00:21:56,693 --> 00:21:58,324
Take care of the others like always.

278
00:21:58,635 --> 00:22:00,831
And be extra careful too.

279
00:22:01,151 --> 00:22:01,955
Yes, Coach.

280
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:08,586
Let's go!

281
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,088
Tiger!

282
00:22:20,902 --> 00:22:21,866
Inside!

283
00:22:25,551 --> 00:22:26,942
Left, left!

284
00:22:31,866 --> 00:22:32,800
Yes!

285
00:22:45,755 --> 00:22:47,342
Hey, they're coming. Block them!

286
00:23:10,186 --> 00:23:12,653
Nao! Nao! Shoot it, Duennao!

287
00:23:27,951 --> 00:23:29,008
I'm freaking exhausted.

288
00:23:30,111 --> 00:23:30,826
Seriously.

289
00:23:31,271 --> 00:23:32,946
Mick, Field.

290
00:23:33,524 --> 00:23:34,573
You guys okay?

291
00:23:35,044 --> 00:23:36,404
- I'm okay.
- Thanks, guys.

292
00:23:36,728 --> 00:23:38,288
But it's obvious they did it on purpose.

293
00:23:39,195 --> 00:23:39,920
Seriously.

294
00:23:40,071 --> 00:23:42,768
So what should we do now?

295
00:23:44,075 --> 00:23:45,511
They're definitely gonna play rough.

296
00:23:45,622 --> 00:23:48,586
We don't need to risk ourselves. We're already ahead on points.

297
00:23:48,964 --> 00:23:52,155
We'll play defensively. Protect yourselves and focus on defense.

298
00:23:52,288 --> 00:23:53,164
Okay?

299
00:23:54,924 --> 00:23:57,466
Hey, you guys, be careful.

300
00:23:57,840 --> 00:23:59,644
They're definitely gonna play rough.

301
00:24:00,960 --> 00:24:04,213
Don't get yourselves injured.
This is just a friendly football match.

302
00:24:04,835 --> 00:24:06,466
No need to take it too seriously, okay?

303
00:24:07,644 --> 00:24:10,760
We've got a big tournament next month. Getting hurt now would suck.

304
00:24:13,093 --> 00:24:15,511
Let's go, for the Premier League!

305
00:24:15,875 --> 00:24:16,995
Premier League!

306
00:24:17,848 --> 00:24:19,662
No way.

307
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:35,897
Hey, Nao!

308
00:24:36,066 --> 00:24:36,820
Hey!

309
00:24:41,275 --> 00:24:42,520
Hey, calm down!

310
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,324
Calm down!

311
00:24:44,657 --> 00:24:45,462
Hey!

312
00:24:45,711 --> 00:24:46,740
Hey, hey!

313
00:24:46,826 --> 00:24:47,831
Hey, stop!

314
00:24:48,928 --> 00:24:49,888
What the fuck is wrong with you, huh?

315
00:24:50,017 --> 00:24:51,653
Huh? Huh?

316
00:24:51,764 --> 00:24:52,822
Suer!

317
00:24:53,008 --> 00:24:54,191
Get a hold of yourself!

318
00:24:54,946 --> 00:24:55,884
That's enough.

319
00:24:58,422 --> 00:24:59,875
My knee's just scraped a little.

320
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:01,968
Shit, let me see your leg.

321
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,480
Go treat your wound first.

322
00:25:05,728 --> 00:25:08,182
- I'll go get the first aid kit.
- Stop worrying about me.

323
00:25:08,248 --> 00:25:09,240
Look over there.

324
00:25:10,253 --> 00:25:12,715
Calm down and check on the others.

325
00:25:12,893 --> 00:25:14,635
Break it up, guys!

326
00:25:20,586 --> 00:25:21,884
Mick, let me see.

327
00:25:22,475 --> 00:25:24,515
Coach, this hurts like hell.

328
00:25:25,866 --> 00:25:26,760
Look at this.

329
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:30,137
That fucking hurts.

330
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:31,840
Hey.

331
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:33,410
You're asking for it now.

332
00:25:37,937 --> 00:25:39,253
Who started it?

333
00:25:42,626 --> 00:25:44,875
I asked who started it.

334
00:25:45,844 --> 00:25:47,062
How could you all

335
00:25:47,431 --> 00:25:49,164
bring shame to the school like this?

336
00:25:56,031 --> 00:25:57,420
If nobody admits it,

337
00:25:59,048 --> 00:26:00,884
I'll expel every single one of you.

338
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:02,795
It was me.

339
00:26:04,915 --> 00:26:06,608
I was the one who told everyone to do it.

340
00:26:08,684 --> 00:26:09,831
Hey, Suer—

341
00:26:11,777 --> 00:26:12,826
Gunnathee.

342
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:15,871
You're the team captain.

343
00:26:18,057 --> 00:26:21,262
- Why would you do something like this?
- You might not believe me,

344
00:26:21,546 --> 00:26:23,866
but their side started it first.

345
00:26:24,133 --> 00:26:25,640
And they hurt my teammates too.

346
00:26:26,706 --> 00:26:29,031
Is this really how athletes are supposed to act?

347
00:26:30,053 --> 00:26:31,528
Those guys started it first, sir.

348
00:26:31,773 --> 00:26:35,271
We were just trying to stop them. The captain isn't the only one at fault.

349
00:26:36,231 --> 00:26:38,964
That's right, sir. I was just standing there and still got hit too.

350
00:26:39,351 --> 00:26:40,955
I didn't even get to hit back once.

351
00:26:41,471 --> 00:26:43,786
- That's right.
- Sir,

352
00:26:44,537 --> 00:26:46,800
I can vouch for my students.

353
00:26:47,106 --> 00:26:48,760
They really were being careful.

354
00:26:49,311 --> 00:26:51,120
Some of them were just defending themselves.

355
00:26:51,688 --> 00:26:54,364
Maybe they got a little hot-headed. They're teenagers after all.

356
00:26:54,795 --> 00:27:00,448
I think punishing them appropriately should be enough.
Like deducting behavior points

357
00:27:00,751 --> 00:27:02,248
or calling in their parents for a talk.

358
00:27:02,337 --> 00:27:03,906
Please don't expel them.

359
00:27:08,306 --> 00:27:09,422
Mr. Gunnathee,

360
00:27:10,275 --> 00:27:12,448
if you keep behaving like this,

361
00:27:12,866 --> 00:27:15,820
how can you possibly qualify as team captain?

362
00:27:18,368 --> 00:27:20,084
You must take responsibility.

363
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:22,880
You are removed from the football club.

364
00:27:23,346 --> 00:27:25,040
Uh, Sir...

365
00:27:25,444 --> 00:27:28,466
Tiger is the best player in our school.

366
00:27:28,653 --> 00:27:30,737
And he's always been a good captain.

367
00:27:31,142 --> 00:27:32,915
The big competition next month...

368
00:27:33,080 --> 00:27:34,564
we might not win

369
00:27:34,835 --> 00:27:35,977
without him.

370
00:27:45,528 --> 00:27:46,991
You're suspended for one week.

371
00:27:48,457 --> 00:27:51,008
And you'll lose 70 behavior points.

372
00:27:51,297 --> 00:27:52,262
And tomorrow,

373
00:27:52,671 --> 00:27:54,382
bring your parent to meet me.

374
00:27:55,822 --> 00:27:57,280
As for the rest of you,

375
00:27:57,840 --> 00:28:01,942
each of you will lose 50 behavior points.

376
00:28:20,804 --> 00:28:21,693
Suer.

377
00:28:21,986 --> 00:28:23,160
Are you okay?

378
00:28:24,542 --> 00:28:26,380
So are you really getting kicked out of the club?

379
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:29,266
Without Suer on our team,

380
00:28:29,391 --> 00:28:30,595
we're screwed.

381
00:28:31,346 --> 00:28:34,928
Seriously, if Suer hadn't started it today, I would've thrown the first punch.

382
00:28:35,751 --> 00:28:38,057
Sorry for starting it first.

383
00:28:38,555 --> 00:28:40,680
Why the fuck are you apologizing, Suer?

384
00:28:40,977 --> 00:28:43,195
All of us were holding back too.

385
00:28:43,462 --> 00:28:45,888
Besides, they went after Nao first.

386
00:28:46,257 --> 00:28:49,280
If you hadn't started it, one of us would've.

387
00:28:49,991 --> 00:28:51,493
Seriously, who the hell

388
00:28:51,688 --> 00:28:54,364
could put up with that shit? They played dirty as hell.

389
00:28:54,604 --> 00:28:57,506
Yeah, seriously. We didn't start it.

390
00:28:57,831 --> 00:29:00,955
They were about to gang up on you, so I pulled you away and got caught in it instead.

391
00:29:01,386 --> 00:29:03,620
But because I promised you I wouldn't start anything first,

392
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:05,026
I ended up with a busted lip.

393
00:29:05,511 --> 00:29:07,017
Hurts like hell.

394
00:29:07,435 --> 00:29:08,724
You guys...

395
00:29:09,280 --> 00:29:11,937
It's good none of you got seriously hurt. The injuries

396
00:29:12,222 --> 00:29:15,040
aren't too bad. They should heal before the big competition.

397
00:29:15,688 --> 00:29:19,644
But Nao got hit in the knee. Will he be okay?

398
00:29:20,066 --> 00:29:22,382
It's just a scrape. My knee's not busted.

399
00:29:22,595 --> 00:29:24,306
I’m totally fine.

400
00:29:25,653 --> 00:29:27,488
So is Tiger getting kicked out of the club or what?

401
00:29:28,311 --> 00:29:29,644
No one’s told me anything yet.

402
00:29:30,600 --> 00:29:31,480
Alright.

403
00:29:32,044 --> 00:29:33,835
I’ll try talking to the principal again.

404
00:29:34,177 --> 00:29:37,782
We’re screwed next month if we don’t have Tiger.

405
00:29:51,035 --> 00:29:52,560
You’re home, sweetie?

406
00:29:53,275 --> 00:29:54,462
Yeah.

407
00:29:56,782 --> 00:29:57,568
Duen.

408
00:29:57,826 --> 00:29:59,706
What happened to your leg?

409
00:30:00,591 --> 00:30:02,031
What were you out doing this time?

410
00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:03,066
Huh?

411
00:30:03,417 --> 00:30:05,942
It’s fine, Mom. It’ll heal soon.

412
00:30:10,382 --> 00:30:14,511
Tiger, thank you so much for protecting Duen.

413
00:30:15,008 --> 00:30:16,386
Duen too.

414
00:30:16,857 --> 00:30:19,284
How do you even run into someone’s leg like that?

415
00:30:19,533 --> 00:30:21,697
Wait, Mom. So this is my fault?

416
00:30:21,942 --> 00:30:23,422
Well, yeah.

417
00:30:23,693 --> 00:30:26,604
Tiger, did you punch the guy who tripped Duen?

418
00:30:28,004 --> 00:30:30,391
Thanks for getting revenge for him.

419
00:30:31,986 --> 00:30:34,164
- Revenge? Really, Dan?
- Yeah.

420
00:30:34,422 --> 00:30:37,146
If I’d been there, I would’ve been pissed too.

421
00:30:37,288 --> 00:30:41,115
At home, both Mom and I take such good care of you.

422
00:30:41,346 --> 00:30:44,715
- Who the hell do they think they are, hurting Duen?
- Exactly.

423
00:30:44,822 --> 00:30:46,768
It’s good you’re not badly hurt, sweetie.

424
00:30:46,946 --> 00:30:48,835
You only got points deducted anyway.

425
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,764
I used to get that all the time. It’s fine.

426
00:30:55,711 --> 00:30:57,222
Hey, Suer.

427
00:30:57,404 --> 00:30:59,435
You got suspended and they called your guardian too.

428
00:30:59,693 --> 00:31:00,684
What are you gonna do?

429
00:31:00,937 --> 00:31:02,760
Shit, right.

430
00:31:03,484 --> 00:31:06,880
Want me to go instead? I’ll bring snacks for the principal.

431
00:31:07,302 --> 00:31:11,271
- Maybe they’ll go easy on you.
- It’s okay, really.

432
00:31:11,417 --> 00:31:13,862
- I’ll get someone from home to come.
- Alright.

433
00:31:14,026 --> 00:31:16,088
Then don’t stress too much, okay?

434
00:31:16,497 --> 00:31:19,666
The principal will calm down by tomorrow. Trust me.

435
00:31:20,422 --> 00:31:21,106
Okay.

436
00:31:22,582 --> 00:31:23,524
How is it?

437
00:31:23,835 --> 00:31:26,617
- Delicious, right?
- Best thing in the world.

438
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:28,200
Looks like you were starving.

439
00:31:28,586 --> 00:31:29,915
What about you? Hungry?

440
00:31:30,160 --> 00:31:31,271
I’m full already.

441
00:31:36,500 --> 00:31:38,460
Yeah, I’m not really okay.

442
00:31:42,582 --> 00:31:44,448
So who are you gonna ask to come?

443
00:31:46,408 --> 00:31:48,666
Probably my brother. Who else would it be?

444
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:52,702
- Shit, you think he’ll actually come?
- I think so.

445
00:31:53,031 --> 00:31:55,217
- My mom can go with you if you want.
- Nah.

446
00:31:55,888 --> 00:31:57,253
I’d feel bad bothering Aunt Maew.

447
00:31:58,426 --> 00:32:00,284
But if my brother doesn’t come...

448
00:32:01,128 --> 00:32:02,657
Then I’ll have to...

449
00:32:04,506 --> 00:32:08,084
Have to what? Hire someone to pretend to be my guardian or something?

450
00:32:08,671 --> 00:32:10,675
Here’s the thing.

451
00:32:11,022 --> 00:32:14,031
Try calling your brother first. If he doesn’t come,

452
00:32:14,231 --> 00:32:15,795
my mom can go instead.

453
00:32:16,733 --> 00:32:18,062
- Let’s do that.
- No.

454
00:32:18,217 --> 00:32:20,511
Call him. You have to go tomorrow.

455
00:32:23,413 --> 00:32:24,662
Come on, just do it.

456
00:32:24,817 --> 00:32:26,644
- No.
- Call him.

457
00:32:26,755 --> 00:32:28,040
Or I’m bringing my mom.

458
00:32:36,831 --> 00:32:38,608
- What is it?
- You free tomorrow?

459
00:32:38,853 --> 00:32:40,013
I need a small favor.

460
00:32:40,626 --> 00:32:41,462
What kind of favor?

461
00:32:41,782 --> 00:32:45,124
I got into a fight with students from another school.

462
00:32:45,626 --> 00:32:48,822
At the football event.
I was the one who started it too.

463
00:32:49,857 --> 00:32:51,413
So the principal...

464
00:32:51,675 --> 00:32:55,960
- wants to see my guardian tomorrow.
- What else did you get besides that?

465
00:32:56,533 --> 00:32:58,631
Behavior points deducted.

466
00:32:59,706 --> 00:33:00,740
And suspended for a week.

467
00:33:01,337 --> 00:33:03,995
- But if you’re busy, it’s okay.
- I’ll go tomorrow.

468
00:33:04,142 --> 00:33:05,080
What time?

469
00:33:05,311 --> 00:33:06,746
- Noon.
- Mm.

470
00:33:07,044 --> 00:33:07,964
See you at noon.

471
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,364
What did your brother say?

472
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:13,368
He said he’ll come.

473
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:16,604
Holy shit.

474
00:33:32,431 --> 00:33:33,648
What now?

475
00:33:34,795 --> 00:33:38,502
Ben, think about it. From someone who never had anything before...

476
00:33:39,280 --> 00:33:42,404
to becoming someone acknowledged as his older brother.

477
00:33:43,711 --> 00:33:45,564
Suer got called in because

478
00:33:45,777 --> 00:33:47,364
he got into a fight with another school.

479
00:33:48,457 --> 00:33:49,711
And he asked me to go for him.

480
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:54,595
Well, if anyone’s his guardian, it’d obviously be you.

481
00:33:57,728 --> 00:33:58,835
What do you think I should wear?

482
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:01,946
- Should I get a new suit tailored? Think there’s time?
- Calm down, Singha.

483
00:34:02,186 --> 00:34:03,955
You’re just going to a guardian meeting.

484
00:34:04,186 --> 00:34:10,400
- Why are you making such a big deal out of this?
- Because it’s the first time I get to show up as Suer’s brother.

485
00:34:14,960 --> 00:34:17,751
Ben, help me out here.

486
00:34:19,100 --> 00:34:20,760
Please help me.

487
00:34:26,297 --> 00:34:27,497
Please?

488
00:34:39,084 --> 00:34:40,608
Yeah, yeah.

489
00:35:15,648 --> 00:35:16,591
Where are you?

490
00:35:17,075 --> 00:35:18,400
Just got to the front of the school.

491
00:35:19,013 --> 00:35:20,204
Okay, I’ll come get you.

492
00:35:25,497 --> 00:35:26,382
Ben.

493
00:35:27,631 --> 00:35:28,746
Suer’s coming to get me.

494
00:35:30,791 --> 00:35:31,848
At first I thought

495
00:35:32,071 --> 00:35:33,840
he didn’t want anyone knowing we were related.

496
00:35:34,697 --> 00:35:36,013
But now he’s coming to pick me up.

497
00:36:01,773 --> 00:36:02,808
Did you eat yet?

498
00:36:06,235 --> 00:36:07,146
Yeah.

499
00:36:09,671 --> 00:36:10,457
You?

500
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:15,004
Not yet.

501
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:23,000
Is this the room?

502
00:36:24,302 --> 00:36:24,853
Yeah.

503
00:36:29,226 --> 00:36:30,182
You wait here.

504
00:36:31,048 --> 00:36:33,053
Ben, wait outside.

505
00:36:33,617 --> 00:36:34,711
I don't need to go in with you?

506
00:36:35,084 --> 00:36:36,920
I’ll handle it myself.

507
00:36:42,675 --> 00:36:43,720
What’s he gonna do?

508
00:36:48,764 --> 00:36:50,368
Principal’s Office

509
00:36:51,262 --> 00:36:52,297
Suer.

510
00:36:57,431 --> 00:36:58,591
I just finished eating.

511
00:36:59,044 --> 00:37:00,120
How’d it go?

512
00:37:00,644 --> 00:37:01,915
My brother’s talking to them.

513
00:37:16,524 --> 00:37:17,204
Hey.

514
00:37:18,475 --> 00:37:19,626
I’ll wait over there.

515
00:37:19,906 --> 00:37:21,066
You should talk to your brother first.

516
00:37:23,084 --> 00:37:23,982
Hello.

517
00:37:28,342 --> 00:37:29,435
How’d it go?

518
00:37:29,666 --> 00:37:30,657
It’s settled.

519
00:37:31,266 --> 00:37:32,911
You’re just getting points deducted.

520
00:37:33,520 --> 00:37:34,795
But you’re not suspended.

521
00:37:47,191 --> 00:37:49,000
That kid Tiger stayed with at the house...

522
00:37:49,177 --> 00:37:50,760
I looked into his background.

523
00:37:51,271 --> 00:37:54,097
- Found something interesting.
- What?

524
00:37:54,448 --> 00:37:56,262
That kid’s stepfather...

525
00:37:57,102 --> 00:37:59,262
is part of a rival gang.

526
00:38:00,271 --> 00:38:01,391
But right now...

527
00:38:01,688 --> 00:38:03,782
he’s running things from inside prison.

528
00:38:04,435 --> 00:38:06,955
Or maybe his real father isn’t actually dead?

529
00:38:07,155 --> 00:38:08,524
Then why...

530
00:38:08,711 --> 00:38:10,666
did his mother remarry so quickly?

531
00:38:11,004 --> 00:38:13,777
- You seriously couldn’t find anything else?
- Nope.

532
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:16,555
No matter how much digging we did, nothing came up.

533
00:38:16,768 --> 00:38:19,422
I think he's someone powerful.

534
00:38:19,568 --> 00:38:23,111
That’s why only rumors ever leak out.

535
00:38:29,297 --> 00:38:31,248
What do you know about that kid’s family?

536
00:38:32,586 --> 00:38:33,404
Why?

537
00:38:33,688 --> 00:38:36,031
You’re not planning anything weird, are you?

538
00:38:37,195 --> 00:38:40,071
- I’m warning you, don’t even think about it.
- What the hell are you talking about?

539
00:38:40,191 --> 00:38:41,528
You’re done here. Go home.

540
00:38:46,613 --> 00:38:47,306
Let’s go.

541
00:38:52,226 --> 00:38:54,035
So, how’s Suer doing?

542
00:38:55,431 --> 00:38:56,617
It’s all settled.

543
00:38:57,200 --> 00:38:58,537
Just got points deducted.

544
00:38:58,977 --> 00:39:00,595
But no suspension.

545
00:39:00,751 --> 00:39:02,284
What did your brother do to the principal?

546
00:39:02,937 --> 00:39:05,364
- No clue.
- Damn.

547
00:39:05,586 --> 00:39:07,288
So this is the mafia, huh?

548
00:39:07,702 --> 00:39:09,408
Scary as hell.

549
00:39:11,168 --> 00:39:12,791
But even if he looks intimidating...

550
00:39:13,186 --> 00:39:14,808
your brother doesn’t seem that bad.

551
00:39:15,444 --> 00:39:17,804
- Don’t you wanna talk things out with him?
- Nah.

552
00:39:18,031 --> 00:39:20,328
He was talking nonsense earlier anyway.

553
00:39:20,902 --> 00:39:23,244
Alright, suit yourself.

554
00:39:24,982 --> 00:39:26,133
Hey, Suer.

555
00:39:26,848 --> 00:39:29,053
Take me shopping for report supplies tonight.

556
00:39:29,657 --> 00:39:32,155
It’s due soon and I haven’t started.

557
00:39:32,853 --> 00:39:35,151
- Sure.
- Alright, see you tonight.

558
00:39:47,493 --> 00:39:48,840
Suer.

559
00:39:49,804 --> 00:39:50,546
Huh?

560
00:39:50,764 --> 00:39:53,013
I seriously hate biker punks.

561
00:39:53,084 --> 00:39:55,653
They’re annoying as hell. Their exhaust pipes are so loud.

562
00:39:55,697 --> 00:39:59,191
- Mine’s loud too and you never complain.
- That’s different, asshole. These guys are deafening.

563
00:40:03,746 --> 00:40:04,697
What?

564
00:40:07,831 --> 00:40:09,026
You’re Duennao, right?

565
00:40:10,435 --> 00:40:12,120
Yeah. Why?

566
00:40:12,666 --> 00:40:13,511
What is it?

567
00:40:14,542 --> 00:40:15,693
Do you know Manao?

568
00:40:15,844 --> 00:40:17,906
- Huh?
- I asked if you know Manao.

569
00:40:19,844 --> 00:40:20,764
Manao?

570
00:40:22,266 --> 00:40:25,204
- Oh, Manao.
- So you do know her.

571
00:40:25,460 --> 00:40:26,777
Why are you messing with my girlfriend?

572
00:40:26,800 --> 00:40:28,320
- She texted me first.
- Don’t make excuses.

573
00:40:28,377 --> 00:40:31,000
- Hey, get him!
- Cops!

574
00:40:33,613 --> 00:40:35,133
Go after him!

575
00:41:01,466 --> 00:41:02,284
Come here first.

576
00:41:17,235 --> 00:41:18,724
I’m exhausted.

577
00:41:20,435 --> 00:41:22,120
I asked if you know Manao.

578
00:41:23,248 --> 00:41:24,120
Suer.

579
00:41:24,220 --> 00:41:25,306
What’s wrong with you?

580
00:41:26,084 --> 00:41:28,555
So you know Manao too? Or did she text you too?

581
00:41:28,964 --> 00:41:31,213
Or were you talking to her and started liking her?

582
00:41:31,368 --> 00:41:34,342
And when you found out she had a boyfriend, you got like this?

583
00:41:36,444 --> 00:41:38,848
Suer, get a grip.

584
00:41:39,751 --> 00:41:42,844
Do you like her or something?

585
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:44,622
I don’t like her.

586
00:41:45,004 --> 00:41:47,448
I’m still confused why she even texted me.

587
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,888
But I think she just texts everyone.

588
00:41:50,302 --> 00:41:51,933
Calm down, Suer.

589
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:54,453
Don’t mess with someone who already has a boyfriend.

590
00:41:56,591 --> 00:41:58,808
You already have a girlfriend, right?

591
00:41:59,080 --> 00:41:59,884
Huh?

592
00:42:01,977 --> 00:42:05,017
Suer, how could I have a girlfriend? I don’t.

593
00:42:05,235 --> 00:42:06,617
What are you confused about?

594
00:42:08,235 --> 00:42:11,448
- But you were talking to her.
- I wasn’t.

595
00:42:12,324 --> 00:42:13,826
Do you really like her that much?

596
00:42:14,777 --> 00:42:16,973
- Like her?
- Yeah.

597
00:42:17,297 --> 00:42:18,826
Do you really like her that much?

598
00:42:20,657 --> 00:42:21,986
For real?

599
00:42:28,644 --> 00:42:30,244
Hey, Suer.

600
00:42:30,511 --> 00:42:32,528
Do you really like her that much?

601
00:42:33,311 --> 00:42:34,820
She already has a boyfriend.

602
00:42:38,168 --> 00:42:41,244
I think you’ll meet someone better someday.

603
00:42:41,573 --> 00:42:43,071
Someone who truly loves you.

604
00:42:43,204 --> 00:42:44,471
You should move on.

605
00:42:44,764 --> 00:42:48,582
- But I don’t want to like anyone else.
- Then what do you want me to do?

606
00:42:48,848 --> 00:42:52,302
- Can you stop talking to her?
- Yeah, okay.

607
00:42:56,088 --> 00:42:57,706
- Really?
- Really.

608
00:43:03,062 --> 00:43:04,140
Hey.

609
00:43:07,413 --> 00:43:09,777
Let’s stop talking and stop getting involved with each other.

610
00:43:10,160 --> 00:43:11,231
Okay?

611
00:43:12,275 --> 00:43:14,373
Don’t you like her?

612
00:43:14,595 --> 00:43:15,680
I don’t.

613
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:17,860
I never liked her in the first place.

614
00:43:20,022 --> 00:43:20,955
Swear it.

615
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:23,373
Promise me instead.

616
00:43:26,808 --> 00:43:27,942
I promise.

617
00:43:31,955 --> 00:43:32,862
Let’s go home.

618
00:43:33,540 --> 00:43:34,337
Let’s go.

619
00:43:38,884 --> 00:43:39,657
What?

620
00:43:40,235 --> 00:43:41,577
Come on. Aren’t we leaving?

621
00:43:41,880 --> 00:43:42,808
Yeah, let’s go.

622
00:43:47,706 --> 00:43:48,844
Shit, are they still here?

623
00:43:50,040 --> 00:43:50,888
What are you scared of?

624
00:44:01,742 --> 00:44:02,666
Suer.

625
00:44:09,751 --> 00:44:10,700
What’s wrong?

626
00:44:15,235 --> 00:44:16,355
Are you sick?

627
00:44:34,817 --> 00:44:36,537
Hey.

628
00:44:38,297 --> 00:44:39,551
I’m fine.

629
00:44:40,100 --> 00:44:42,351
Oh right, you’ve got work to do, right?

630
00:44:43,062 --> 00:44:44,773
I’ve got stuff too.

631
00:44:47,857 --> 00:44:49,800
I’m not sleeping here tonight.

632
00:44:55,515 --> 00:44:56,613
What’s with him?

633
00:45:30,635 --> 00:45:31,853
Ow.

634
00:45:36,191 --> 00:45:37,391
Suer.

635
00:45:40,915 --> 00:45:44,524
What’s with you today? Aren’t you sleeping over at Nao’s place?

636
00:45:45,391 --> 00:45:48,826
- Can you not say that name?
- What’s wrong with you? Did you guys fight?

637
00:45:51,524 --> 00:45:52,373
Yeah.

638
00:45:52,817 --> 00:45:54,262
So now you’re sleeping in my room?

639
00:45:56,880 --> 00:45:59,208
Whatever you fought about, just talk it out properly.

640
00:45:59,306 --> 00:46:01,137
Stop acting like a kid.

641
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:02,337
No.

642
00:46:02,751 --> 00:46:04,857
No? What do you mean “no”?

643
00:46:05,075 --> 00:46:07,644
You don’t want to be friends with him anymore or what?

644
00:46:08,133 --> 00:46:11,795
- Friends?
- Yeah. You wanted to be friends with Nao, didn’t you?

645
00:46:13,088 --> 00:46:15,813
No. No. I don’t want to be friends.

646
00:46:15,880 --> 00:46:18,280
Calm down first. Was it that serious?

647
00:46:19,284 --> 00:46:20,435
Suer.

648
00:46:20,488 --> 00:46:22,853
My bed, Suer. Be careful with it.

649
00:46:33,360 --> 00:46:35,275
Hey Suer, let me ask you something.

650
00:46:35,640 --> 00:46:37,555
Did you and Nao really fight that badly?

651
00:46:37,700 --> 00:46:40,088
To the point you’re eating at another restaurant like this?

652
00:46:48,626 --> 00:46:51,488
- Move, Nao’s here.
- What are you doing?

653
00:46:51,582 --> 00:46:53,173
Do you think you’re tiny or something?

654
00:46:54,253 --> 00:46:55,520
Did he leave yet?

655
00:46:56,733 --> 00:47:00,417
- He’s still standing in front of the shop.
- Let him leave first.

656
00:47:00,546 --> 00:47:02,840
- Then we’ll go.
- Why? We can’t.

657
00:47:03,106 --> 00:47:06,404
- School’s about to start. We have to go.
- If we go out now, I’m dead, asshole!

658
00:47:06,502 --> 00:47:09,671
Why though? You guys just had a fight.

659
00:47:10,035 --> 00:47:12,502
Eating at another restaurant isn’t weird.

660
00:47:15,560 --> 00:47:16,706
What’s with you?

661
00:47:16,822 --> 00:47:19,057
Or maybe you guys didn’t just fight?

662
00:47:19,946 --> 00:47:21,244
Did he do something to you?

663
00:47:23,555 --> 00:47:25,960
Suer, I’m not joking.

664
00:47:26,471 --> 00:47:28,848
- Did he do something to you?
- He didn’t do anything.

665
00:47:29,191 --> 00:47:31,186
Just help me figure out how to escape first, damn it. Hurry.

666
00:47:31,608 --> 00:47:34,186
It’s really not a big deal. We’re just eating here. Let’s go.

667
00:47:34,271 --> 00:47:36,266
- Hey, where are you going?
- Hurry or we’ll be late.

668
00:47:55,040 --> 00:47:56,662
Eating at my rival’s restaurant, huh?

669
00:47:56,920 --> 00:47:57,733
Is it good?

670
00:48:01,980 --> 00:48:04,151
You really are such an ungrateful brat.

671
00:48:04,591 --> 00:48:05,422
But whatever.

672
00:48:07,040 --> 00:48:08,071
Hey.

673
00:48:08,328 --> 00:48:10,626
- Are you mad at me or something?
- No.

674
00:48:10,715 --> 00:48:14,591
- Why would I be upset with you?
- You’ve been acting weird since yesterday.

675
00:48:14,755 --> 00:48:16,200
Yesterday you slept in Field’s room.

676
00:48:16,373 --> 00:48:20,080
And today you’re eating at another restaurant too. Hmm?

677
00:48:20,173 --> 00:48:22,453
Did you guys fight or something?

678
00:48:22,755 --> 00:48:25,666
- Fight about what? Did we fight?
- No.

679
00:48:25,960 --> 00:48:26,795
Nope.

680
00:48:27,168 --> 00:48:28,080
Huh.

681
00:48:29,857 --> 00:48:31,191
You got something to tell me?

682
00:48:32,506 --> 00:48:34,617
Nothing at all, sir.

683
00:48:34,680 --> 00:48:36,173
- This idiot just talks nonsense.
- Huh?

684
00:48:36,453 --> 00:48:38,111
Uh, yeah.

685
00:48:40,102 --> 00:48:41,666
- You sure?
- Yeah.

686
00:48:41,760 --> 00:48:46,360
- I just missed him, so I slept in his room.
- Yeah, you missed me too.

687
00:48:47,422 --> 00:48:49,848
- You’re really okay, right?
- I’m fine.

688
00:48:49,977 --> 00:48:51,973
Totally fine.

689
00:48:54,970 --> 00:48:56,475
Alright then, good.

690
00:48:56,964 --> 00:48:58,000
Let’s go to class.

691
00:48:59,777 --> 00:49:01,462
Let’s go study.

692
00:49:06,657 --> 00:49:07,986
Asshole.

693
00:49:08,946 --> 00:49:10,004
That hurts.

694
00:49:10,164 --> 00:49:11,271
Asshole.

695
00:49:13,093 --> 00:49:13,955
So?

696
00:49:14,346 --> 00:49:16,684
Was the food you ate today good? Huh?

697
00:49:20,733 --> 00:49:21,831
Was it good?

698
00:49:23,000 --> 00:49:24,213
- Yeah.
- Oh really?

699
00:49:25,364 --> 00:49:27,088
You’re supposed to say it wasn’t good.

700
00:49:27,186 --> 00:49:29,235
- It wasn’t good.
- Yeah.

701
00:49:29,582 --> 00:49:31,675
- But it’s still better than his mom’s food.
- Hey.

702
00:49:31,737 --> 00:49:32,924
I’m gonna smack your mouth.

703
00:49:38,462 --> 00:49:40,431
Hey, Suer. Does this shirt suit me?

704
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,528
Yeah, it looks good.

705
00:49:46,644 --> 00:49:48,502
Is that Suer’s shirt?

706
00:49:48,728 --> 00:49:50,315
Yeah. Suer gave it to me.

707
00:49:50,417 --> 00:49:51,982
Seriously?

708
00:49:52,582 --> 00:49:55,740
Yeah. He gave me a whole bunch. Almost his entire closet.

709
00:49:55,808 --> 00:49:58,000
His whole closet too?

710
00:49:58,066 --> 00:49:59,062
Yeah.

711
00:50:00,520 --> 00:50:01,866
Yeah, I think

712
00:50:02,280 --> 00:50:03,580
we should hurry up.

713
00:50:04,608 --> 00:50:05,688
We’re gonna be late.

714
00:50:05,973 --> 00:50:06,857
Yeah, let’s go.

715
00:50:23,386 --> 00:50:24,386
Stayed up late?

716
00:50:24,982 --> 00:50:27,320
Yeah. Didn’t sleep much.

717
00:50:29,000 --> 00:50:30,266
What class do you guys have today?

718
00:50:31,413 --> 00:50:33,822
No idea. Maybe math.

719
00:50:34,600 --> 00:50:36,213
Alright then, I’m heading to class first.

720
00:50:37,013 --> 00:50:38,097
See you guys.

721
00:50:44,120 --> 00:50:45,391
Hold up, Suer.

722
00:50:45,697 --> 00:50:47,128
- What?
- Is there something you wanna tell me?

723
00:50:48,440 --> 00:50:49,480
Like what?

724
00:50:57,706 --> 00:51:00,364
Why are you going “hm?” and asking if I’ve got something to tell you?

725
00:51:01,373 --> 00:51:03,386
If you’re suspicious about something, just say it.

726
00:51:05,933 --> 00:51:07,844
Did Nao hurt you or something?

727
00:51:08,662 --> 00:51:10,426
- Huh?
- I mean...

728
00:51:10,848 --> 00:51:15,053
That thing about him being a gang leader is true, right? The thing people joke about.

729
00:51:16,195 --> 00:51:17,346
What do you mean?

730
00:51:18,204 --> 00:51:19,817
I saw him wearing your shirt.

731
00:51:20,020 --> 00:51:21,417
How’s that even possible?

732
00:51:21,751 --> 00:51:23,768
You’re super possessive of your stuff.

733
00:51:24,191 --> 00:51:25,631
Did he threaten you?

734
00:51:27,860 --> 00:51:29,760
He didn’t threaten me or anything.

735
00:51:29,991 --> 00:51:31,820
I just wanted to give it to him.

736
00:51:33,120 --> 00:51:37,444
How is that possible? A guy like you willingly giving someone your stuff that easily?

737
00:51:41,497 --> 00:51:42,217
Hm?

738
00:51:45,220 --> 00:51:47,977
You can keep a secret, right?

739
00:51:50,613 --> 00:51:51,693
Then this Saturday,

740
00:51:52,222 --> 00:51:54,831
I’ll come to your room. Tell Mick too.

741
00:51:55,164 --> 00:51:57,955
- I’ll tell you my secret myself.
- Secret?

742
00:51:58,671 --> 00:51:59,746
What secret?

743
00:52:00,000 --> 00:52:03,560
- About Nao hurting you?
- Hurt me how? No.

744
00:52:03,702 --> 00:52:04,502
You sure?

745
00:52:05,484 --> 00:52:06,844
Yeah, seriously.

746
00:52:08,071 --> 00:52:10,728
That’s a relief. I thought something happened.

747
00:52:10,906 --> 00:52:12,328
Come on, let’s go to class.

748
00:52:18,604 --> 00:52:20,102
Nosy bastard.

749
00:52:24,586 --> 00:52:25,764
You at class yet?

750
00:52:30,017 --> 00:52:30,906
Not yet.

751
00:52:31,386 --> 00:52:32,346
What’s up?

752
00:52:33,426 --> 00:52:35,622
Nothing. You coming home today?

753
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:41,466
When you figure things out, let me know.

754
00:52:41,680 --> 00:52:44,191
I thought you were gonna cry somewhere else and refuse to come home.

755
00:52:44,822 --> 00:52:46,048
I’m worried about you.

756
00:53:08,288 --> 00:53:11,017
We’re gonna be in 11th grade soon. Time flies, huh?

757
00:53:11,457 --> 00:53:12,777
And I’m turning 17 soon.

758
00:53:13,093 --> 00:53:16,546
- Get ready to call me big bro.
- We’re only two months apart and you want me to call you that?

759
00:53:16,826 --> 00:53:18,960
I’m seven years younger than Singha and I still don’t call him “P’.”

760
00:53:19,115 --> 00:53:21,742
By the way, about your brother… aren’t you gonna talk to him?

761
00:53:22,440 --> 00:53:24,617
- What?
- Ben, this is serious.

762
00:53:24,822 --> 00:53:26,342
Get over here right now.

763
00:53:26,400 --> 00:53:27,964
Why do I have a boss like you?

764
00:53:28,328 --> 00:53:30,200
Aren’t you excited at all?

765
00:53:30,346 --> 00:53:32,880
Nope. I wasn’t excited the first time either.

766
00:53:33,133 --> 00:53:35,777
See? That’s exactly what’s making me even more stressed out.

767
00:53:35,875 --> 00:53:36,942
Asshole.
